### CallDesk CRM API Testing Samples
### Use with VS Code REST Client or any HTTP tool.

@baseUrl = http://localhost/calldesk/api
@apiKey = YOUR_ORG_API_KEY_FROM_SETTINGS

# 1. CREATE A NEW LEAD
# Endpoint: leads.php (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/leads.php
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

name=Jane Doe&
mobile=9876543210&
status=New&
remarks=Automated via HTTP API

###

# 2. ASSIGN LEAD TO EXECUTIVE
# Endpoint: assign.php (POST)
# Required: lead_id, assign_to (Executive User ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/assign.php
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

lead_id=123&
assign_to=5

###

# 3. GET LIST OF FOLLOW-UPS (TODAY'S TASK)
# Endpoint: followups.php (GET)
GET {{baseUrl}}/followups.php?date_filter=today
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}

###

# 4. SEND AUTOMATED WHATSAPP (Via Green-API)
# Endpoint: send_whatsapp.php (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/send_whatsapp.php
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

mobile=919876543210&
message=Hi, your ticket #4321 has been updated. CallDesk CRM.

###

# 5. UPLOAD CALL RECORDING
# Endpoint: upload_recording.php (POST)
# Uses multipart/form-data. In a real tool like cURL, use --form.
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload_recording.php
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary123

--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="recording"; filename="call_recording.mp3"
Content-Type: audio/mpeg

< ./sample_recording.mp3
--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="mobile"

9876543210
--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="call_time"

2026-03-21 22:30:00
--boundary123--
